ETIC DATA GENERATOR\r\n# ============================================================================\r\n\r\ndef generate_pulse_sequence(n_pulses=100, causal_ratio=0.3):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Generate synthetic pulse sequence with controllable causal structure.\r\n    \r\n    - causal_tokens: appear in semantically related pulses (true research trajectory)\r\n    - noise_tokens: appear randomly (metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    causal_tokens = [f\"causal_{i}\" for i in range(20)]\r\n    noise_tokens = [f\"noise_{i}\" for i in range(80)]\r\n    \r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for i in range(n_pulses):\r\n        pulse = []\r\n        # Add 2-4 causal tokens (based on previous pulse's causal content)\r\n        n_causal = random.randint(2, 4)\r\n        if i > 0 and random.random() < 0.8:  # 80% chance of causal continuity\r\n            prev_causal = [t for t in pulses[-1] if t.startswith(\"causal_\")]\r\n            if prev_causal:\r\n                pulse.extend(random.sample(prev_causal, min(n_causal, len(prev_causal))))\r\n        pulse.extend(random.sample(causal_tokens, n_causal))\r\n        \r\n        # Add 5-10 noise tokens (random, no temporal structure)\r\n        n_noise = random.randint(5, 10)\r\n        pulse.extend(random.sample(noise_tokens, n_noise))\r\n        \r\n        random.shuffle(pulse)\r\n        pulses.append(pulse)\r\n    \r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\n# ============================================================================\r\n# COMPRESSION METHODS\r\n# ============================================================================\r\n\r\ndef compute_frequencies(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Standard frequency-based compression (like current Breakaway).\"\"\"\r\n    all_tokens = [t for pulse in pulses for t in pulse]\r\n    freq = Counter(all_tokens)\r\n    return freq\r\n\r\ndef compute_cfi(pulses, window=5):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Compute Causal Fidelity Index for each token.\r\n    \r\n    CFI = probability token appears in context of its own causal cluster\r\n    vs random appearance in corpus.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    all_tokens = [t for pulse in pulses for t in pulse]\r\n    total_count = len(all_tokens)\r\n    corpus_freq = Counter(all_tokens)\r\n    \r\n    cfi_scores = {}\r\n    for token in corpus_freq:\r\n        # Count appearances in causal-adjacent context\r\n        causal_count = 0\r\n        for i, pulse in enumerate(pulses):\r\n            if token in pulse:\r\n                # Check if previous pulse had related causal tokens\r\n                for j in range(max(0,\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:08:28"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":788,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 100757\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: scripts/tic_experiment.ps1 (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and decide on ONE concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE (Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec)\r\n- CFI Analysis is DONE (2026-03-24)\r\n- Next pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe key insight from CFI_RESULTS.md:\r\n- 44.8% of invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise/metaprogramming artifacts)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181\r\n\r\nThe next step is clear: implement a CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would:\r\n1. Weight invariants by their CFI score\r\n2. Compare prediction accuracy vs frequency baseline\r\n3. Test if high-CFI invariants are better predictors\r\n\r\nLet me create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the frequency-invariant data\r\n2. Applies CFI weighting\r\n3. Compares next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nFirst, I need to look at what data is available. The CFI_RESULTS.md mentions there are analysis scripts. Let me check if there's a scripts directory or if I need to create the exper