{"type":"message","id":"52987ee1","parentId":"50fab14c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:11:09.707Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_sh7akzbuypvd_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tuesday, March 24, 2026 10:11:03 AM\r\n---\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 101045\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI analysis is done, showing 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next action would be to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment as noted in the pending items. This involves comparing CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nI should look at the current research files to understand the baseline and then design the experiment. Let me check what's in the research directory.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items:\r\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n\r\nThis is the most logical next step. I need to:\r\n1. Check the existing frequency invariants file (from CFI analysis)\r\n2. Design a simple experiment that compares CFI-weighted selection vs pure frequency selection\r\n3. Implement and run it\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and design the experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis reveals 44.8% of invariants are pure noise. The pending priority is implementing the CFI-weighted compression experiment to validate whether CFI-scoring improves next-pulse prediction over frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment that compares CFI-weighted invariant selection against frequency-only baseline for next-pulse prediction quality.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```old_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Goal:** Compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction quality\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted selection (filtering noise invariants CFI=0) should outperform frequency-only selection because:\r\n1. Removes metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) that don't reflect actual causal structure\r\n2. Prioritizes true research trajectory invariants (CFI>0.7)\r\n3. Reduces contamination from constant-format noise\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n- Rank invariants by frequency (descending)\r\n- Select top-N for context\r\n- Measure prediction quality\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression  \r\n- Filter: CFI > 0.5 (remove noise)\r\n- Rank remaining by: score = CFI * log(frequency)\r\n- Select top-N for context\r\n- Measure prediction quality\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Prediction Quality\r\nCompare coherence/continuity of:\r\n- What the agent ACTUALLY did next pulse\r\n- What the compressed context would have predicted\r\n\r\n## Implementation Checklist\r\n- [ ] Extract CFI scores from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n- [ ] Build frequency inventory of current invariants\r\n- [ ] Implement both selection algorithms\r\n- [ ] Run both on same pulse context\r\n- [ ] Compare prediction fidelity scores\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted should show 15-30% improvement in prediction coherence\r\n(if hypothesis holds)\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:11:03"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":767,"aggregated":"Tuesday, March 24, 2026 10:11:03 AM\r\n---\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 101045\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action would best advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI analysis is done, showing 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next action would be to run the CFI-weighted compression experiment as noted in the pending items. This involves comparing CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nI should look at the current research files to understand the baseline and then design the experiment. Let me check what's in the research directory.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending items:\r\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n\r\nThis is the most logical next step. I need to:\r\n1. Check the existing frequency invariants file (from CFI analysis)\r\n2. Design a simple experiment that compares CFI-weighted selection vs pure frequency selection\r\n3. Implement and run it\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and design the experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis reveals 44.8% of invariants are pure noise. The pending priority is implementing the CFI-weighted compression experiment to validate whether CFI-scoring improves next-pulse prediction over frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nDesign and implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment that compares CFI-weighted invariant selection against frequency-only baseline for next-pulse prediction quality.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```old_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Date:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Goal:** Compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction quality\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted selection (filtering noise invariants CFI=0) should outperform frequency-only selection because:\r\n1. Removes metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) that don't reflect actual causal structure\r\n2. Prioritizes true research trajectory invariants (CFI>0.7)\r\n3. Reduces contamination from constant-format noise\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n- Rank invariants by frequency (descending)\r\n- Select top-N for context\r\n- Measure prediction quality\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression  \r\n- Filter: CFI > 0.5 (remove noise)\r\n- Rank remaining by: score = CFI * log(frequency)\r\n- Select top-N for context\r\n- Measure prediction quality\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Prediction Quality\r\nCompare coherence/continuity of:\r\n- What the agent ACTUALLY did next pulse\r\n- What the compressed context would have predicted\r\n\r\n## Implementation Checklist\r\n- [ ] Extract CFI scores from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\r\n- [ ] Build frequency inventory of current invariants\r\n- [ ] Implement both selection algorithms\r\n- [ ] Run both on same pulse context\r\n- [ ] Compare prediction fidelity scores\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted should show 15-30% improvement in prediction coherence\r\n(if hypothesis holds)\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:11:03","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361469705}}
